          <ul class="card-text">Perfect start to the weekend with Eggs en Cocotte 🐣. 
            It’s so easy and has an air of fancy that makes a weekend breakfast feel extra special. 
            Bake an egg with a dash of milk and 🍅 🧀 🌿 🥓 voilá!
            <p></p>
            <li class="list-unstyled">Ingredients:
              <ul>
                <li> Butter </li>
                <li> Minced Tomatoes</li>
                <li> Cooked Bacon</li>
                <li> Basil </li>
                <li> Parmesan Cheese </li>
                <li> Eggs</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <p></p>
            <p> Preparation: </p>
            Pre-heat the oven to 375°F. Crack eggs into a buttered casserole dish one at a time, making sure egg yolks remain intact. 
            Add diced tomatoes, bacon, basil, and cheese. 
            Bake until the whites are set: 12-15 minutes for runny yolks
