            My dear friend Macareba gave me this recipe 3 years ago. 
            These waffles became our tradition on Sunday mornings after partying at El Centro in DC. 
            Maca wrote down the recipe on a piece of paper that still have it hanging off my fridge.
            <p></p>
            <li class="list-unstyled">Wet Ingredients:
              <ul>
                <li> 2 bananas </li>
                <li> 3 eggs</li>
                <li> 1 cup of Greek yogurt</li>
                <li> 1 cup of almond milk </li>
                <li> 1 tsp of vanilla extract </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="list-unstyled">Dry Ingredients:
              <ul>
                <li> 2 cups of whole oats </li>
                <li> 4 tbsp of ground flaxseeds</li>
                <li> 1 tsp of salt</li>
                <li> 1 tsp cinnamon </li>
                <li> 1 tsp of baking powder</li>
                <li> 1 scoop of protein powder</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <p></p>
            <p> Preparation: </p>
            Mix dry and wet ingredients separately and then combine together in a bowl. 
            Finally place the mix on a hot pan or waffle maker. 
            The mix can be used for waffles or pancakes. Enjoy!
